{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3422392,"name":"","username":"ChocolateFreckle","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/chocolatefreckle/{size}/232350_2.png","created_at":"2024-09-10T17:57:10.802Z","cooked":"<p>Our team codes in Java and is struggling to write a method that shuts off our motors when the sensor detects a note within 100mm from the intake. This is the method I’ve currently written:</p>
<p>public void shootOff(){<br>
IntakeSensor.getMeasurement();<br>
if (LaserCan.LASERCAN_STATUS_VALID_MEASUREMENT&lt;=100){<br>
IntakeFeedMotor.set(0);<br>
IntakeCenterMotor.set(0);<br>
LauncherFeedMotor.set(0);<br>
}<br>
}</p>
<p>My objects seem to all be made correctly, what’s bothering me is the LASERCAN_STATUS_VALID_MEASUREMENT, I think I might need to be looking at another int. I’ve linked our GitHub to the post, this method is written in lines 125-132 in Robot Container. Any help would be so appreciated, Thank you so much!</p>
